This paper deals with tracking algorithms and machine learning-based approaches for particle tracking detectors. The use of Deep Convolutional Autoencoder and geometrical space invariances suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of unsupervised learning, which is a common topic in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with experimental results on synthetic and real data, which suggests that it could also belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SD) sub-category.
